<p>I have fixed one Sonar security alert - Array is stored directly by</p>  <p>Initially</p>  <pre><code>void setDerivedKey(byte[] derivedKey) { this.derivedKey = derivedKey; } </code></pre>  <p>To</p>  <pre><code>void setDerivedKey (byte[] newDerivedKey) { if(newDerivedKey==null)  {  this.derivedKey = new byte[0];          } else  {   this.derivedKey = Arrays.copyOf(newDerivedKey, newDerivedKey.length); } }  </code></pre>  <p>How do I fix this</p>  <pre><code>    public pEngine(byte[] salt) {     byte[] mySalt = Arrays.copyOf(salt, salt.length);  //Edited as per below    answer     this.parameters = new pParameters("SomeValue", "SomeValue2", salt, 100); } </code></pre>  <p>What is the Impact of the fix on </p>  <pre><code> Performance  Memory management  Functionality </code></pre>